-1 RULES~
Should you see or be involved in any violation of these rules, speak with
the nearest immortal.  Failing that, direct a note to Akuma who will deal
with the problem at the soonest possible time.

1) No fighting without a PK flag without mutual consent.
2) Respect the Staff.
3) Respect other players.
4) No multiplaying.
5) Don't be an asshole.
6) No botting of any kind.
7) No intentional dropping of link.

Also see 'help disclaimer'.
For more information refer to help pk, multiplay, asshole, botting, and link-dropping.
~

-1 DISCLAIMER~
By continuing to play Genesis you acknowledge that:

(1)  you are willing to abide by the decisions of the Immortals concerning all
     issues involved in the game, and
(2)  conversation and situations may arise during the course of play that may 
     not be suitable for young children.

By these acknowledgments you hereby save and accept Genesis and its 
Administrators from any and all liability that may arise during gameplay.

You also agree that failure to abide by Immortal decisions may result in the 
complete termination of your playing privileges.

By continuing to play here,  you also imply that you are 18 years of age or 
older, Or have parental consent to play here.
~

-1 'Pk Flag' Pkme~
PK is the basis of the mud.  Once you have been flagged PK,
you give up all rights to complain about casual PK not in
violation of the rules.  PK which for some reason violates other rules
will still be dealt with accordingly.
~

-1 Multiplaying~
Multiplay is the act of using one of your characters to in any way
benefit another one of your characters.  Dropping link to give eq/qp,
using other people to transfer eq/qp, and using one character to "avenge"
the death of another one of your characters are all examples of multiplay.
On the basic level, any interaction between characters controlled by the
same player is multiplay.  Also defined under multiplay is the sharing
of characters, and having two people logged in from the same IP.
Your character is your own, you may not sell it, let a friend use it, or
give it away, such acts are sharing of characters.  Two logged players
with the same IP, even should they be different people, is also multiplay.
~

-1 Botting~
Botting is sending commands to the mud while not at the computer and paying
attention.  This means through triggers, macros, tickers, or even spammed
commands.
~

-1 'Link Dropping' link-dropping~
Link Dropping is the act of closing your connection during combat to avoid
being killed or decapitated. Although sometimes people accidentily drop link
during combat, if you do it repeatedly you will be punished.
~

-1 Asshole Pbashing spamkilling permamorting~
Being an asshole includes, but is not limited to, Pbashing, Spam-killing, and
Perma-morting.  Pbashing is insulting other players.  Spam-killing is the
repeated killing of another player.  Perma-morting is morting other players
for long periods of time.  Any form of disrespect and abuse fall into this
category as well.
~



0 Experience~
Experience is earned by killing mobs and is used to improve your character
through the use of the train command.  Experience from mobs is based on their
level and relative strength.  When in a group of two or more, experience is 
split between the group members by the following method.

XP * 2.5, XP / members.

So, a group with 2 members gets slightly better experience, while a group with
a lot of members will get a good bit less, but, in theory, if everyone is
participating every member 'should' be improving the experience output over
time.

Related Helps: Expmod, Stats, and Train.
~


0 Expmod~
Expmod is an experience multiplier that Imms can turn on if they feel that the
players deserve it.  Expmods range in % from 0-250, and can last for up to 300
minutes, or forever.  Example: if a 200% expmod is active, and you kill a mob
worth 500 exp, you will earn 1000 exp instead.  Random and Degrading expmods
can also be activated.  Random will give from 0% to 400% for each kill, and
Degrading expmod will drop by 25% every 15 minutes until it reaches 100%.
Expmod also affects Classpoint gain.  Also, if 10 or more players are logged
on, then there is an additional exp bonus.  Both of these bonuses can be seen
in the who screen if active.

Related Helps: Experience.
~


0 Stats~
The stats are Str, Dex, Con, Int, and Wis.  The max you can train in a stat is 
7 + class reqs.  The XP cost to improve a stat is 10000 * level * level, * 2 if 
over 5.

Str: Improves damage, Raises damcap.
Dex: Lowers speed, Raises avoid/break.
Con: Improves HP regen, Raises soak.
Int: Improves spell power.
Wis: Improves Mana regen, Improves saves.

Regen:      Fighting = 50 * stat, Standing = 150 * stat, Resting = 250 * stat,
            Meditating = 350 * stat.  No PK Fight Timer *= (1 + max (hp|mana) / 20000).
HP Regen:   Monk Rejuvenation, Werewolf, Ninja Orimasu *= 1.5, Vampire Blood *= 2.
Mana Regen: Monk Rejuvenation, Mage, Sorcerer *= 1.5.

Related Helps: Experience, Reqs, and Train.
~


0 Train~
Syntax: train <str/int/wis/dex/con>
Syntax: train <primal/hp/mana>

Train is used to spend experience on your attributes to make them better.  When
starting out, all your attributes are at 1, and your hp and mana are at 10000.
Hp/mana maxes at 100000 and costs your current amount/10 for each point.
Attribute maxes and costs can be found in help stats.

Related Helps: Experience, and Stats.
~


0 Stances~
Syntax: stance <stance>

In combat, the stance of the fighter plays a very important role; you can't 
just stand there and exchange blow for blow unless you are very confident of 
your ability.  Each fighting stance has advantage and disadvantages, the basic 
outline of which follows:

Normal Stances:
BULL: A low aggressive stance.           Bonus: Damage.
CRAB: A low, defensive fighting stance.  Bonus: Soak.
MONGOOSE: A light-footed stance.         Bonus: Avoid
VIPER: A very quick stance.              Bonus: Speed.
CRANE: A wide, sweeping stance.          Bonus: Break.

Advanced Stances:
TIGER: An aggressive, quick stance.      Bonuses: Break, Damage.
 Requires: Bull, Crane.                  Negates: Speed.
DRAGON: A powerful, balanced stance.     Bonuses: Damage, Soak.
 Requires: Crab, Bull.                   Negates: Break.
SWALLOW: An extremely defensive stance.  Bonuses: Soak, Avoid.
 Requires: Crab, Mongoose.               Negates: Damage.
MANTIS: A quick, light-footed stance.    Bonuses: Avoid, Speed.
 Requires: Viper, Mongoose.              Negates: Soak.
MONKEY: A fast, defense-breaking stance. Bonuses: Speed, Break.
 Requires: Viper, Crane.                 Negates: Avoid.

Related Helps: Style and Autostance.
~

0 Autostance~
Syntax: autostance <stance>

By using autostance you will drop into your set stance automatically
when you attack something or get attacked by something. This is an
invaluable command because it allows you eliminate the need to type
'stance <stance>' every time you initiate combat.

Related Helps: Stance.
~

0 Style~
Each style confers a different bonus as listed below.

Unarmed:    - Adds 20% of your skill to avoid and 5% of your skill to break.
            - Confers a chance of an extra attack at 101+.
            - Adds 5% more of your skill to avoid even when not using Unarmed
               style.
 How to use - Wear no weapons or armor in your hands.

Natural:    - Adds 5% of your skill to avoid and 10% of your skill to break.
            - Adds extra damage to all attacks.
 How to use - Wear no weapons or armor in your hands, and use a form with claws.
               *Used instead of unarmed.  Only for classes with NATURAL claws*

One-handed: - Adds 10% of your skill to avoid and 10% of your skill to break.
            - Confers a chance of an extra attack at 1+ and 101+.
 How to use - Wear a weapon in your main hand, and any non-armor in the other.

Shielded:   - Adds 10% of your skill to avoid and 10% of your skill to break.
            - Reduces damage taken.
 How to use - Wear armor in your offhand.

Two-handed: - Adds 5% of your skill to avoid and 20% of your skill to break.
            - Increases damage dealt by weapon attacks.
 How to use - Wear a weapon in your main hand, and nothing in the other, then
               type 'grip'.

Two weapon: - Adds 10% of your skill to break.
            - Confers a chance of an extra main hand attack at 51+ and 151+.
            - Confers a chance of an offhand attack at 1+ and 101+.
 How to use - Wear a weapon in each hand. *Only usable by Drow and Ninja*

Related Helps: Style Table, and Stances.
~

