Middle Areas:
Demon Temple     - 6w2n
Doom             - 4e3n2w6nun
Elemental Caves  - 6e4s2es2eds4undn3en
Gnome Daycare    - 6ed2s
Holy Grove       - 7e
Templars         - 6ed3n2w2nw2n3e2sd2sw

High Areas:
Atlantis         - sd
Drow             - 6e4s2e2s2edwsd
Haif's Town      - 13e
Olympus          - 4e3n2w6n2un
Red Dragon Inn   - 6e4s2es2edwu
Salvnos          - 6e4s2es2edwu6nd2nd
Undead Castle    - 4e4n
~

0 Artifacts~
Artifacts are powerful, unique, unclaimable items which exist at the whim of 
immortals.  Under most circumstances, Artifacts have timers, which means they 
disappear after a set amount of time.  To get an Artifact, participate in 
Immortal Quests, or kill someone with one.  To see what artifacts are currently 
in the game, type Artifact.  In addition to any other affects, Artifacts grant 
a +100 bonus to damcap.

Artifact Listing:
Ring of Hitting - +300 hitroll, +1 attack per round.
*Ring of Damage - +300 damroll, +500 damcap.
Draconic Aura - Sanct, +5000 hp, +100 armor, +50 hit/dam.
The #0Mirror Shades#n of the #0Gods#n - Allows you to see and find anyone.
A Runic Scimitar named 'Magebane' - 50% Magic Resist, dispel magic on hit.
The Sword of Kas - +50 hitroll, +150 damroll, +500 damcap, aggy.
Periapt of Protection - +500 armor, -500 opponent's damcap.

*Artifact is currently in circulation.
~

0 BANK BALANCE DEPOSIT WITHDRAW~
The bank allows players to safely store their gold coins for safekeeping.
You must be in the bank (in Midgaard) to use these commands.

Syntax:
  balance              - Shows your current bank account balance.
  deposit <amount>     - Deposits gold from your inventory into your account.
  withdraw <amount>    - Withdraws gold from your account to your inventory.

Your bank account is tied to your character and will persist even after you
log out, making it a safe place to store excess gold. You can access your
account from the bank in Midgaard.

Related Helps: Quest.
~

0 AUCTION BID SELL~
The auction house allows players to buy and sell items using quest points.
Auctions run for a set duration, with the highest bidder winning the item.

Syntax:
  auction list         - Shows all active auction lots.
  auction info <lot>   - Details about a specific lot.
  auction sell <item> <bid> - Put an item up for auction with a minimum bid.
  auction bid <lot> <amount> - Place a bid on an auction lot.
  auction withdraw <lot> - Cancel your own auction (only if no bids exist).

When you sell an item at auction, it stays available until someone wins it or
the auction expires. If no one bids, you can reclaim your item. The winning
bidder pays in quest points, and the seller receives those quest points.

Related Helps: Quest.
~

0 TRIVIA ANSWER~
Trivia is an automated quiz game where players can earn quest points by answering
questions correctly. Trivia sessions start automatically at regular intervals.

Syntax:
  answer <response>    - Submit your answer to the current trivia question.

When a trivia question is asked, you have a limited time to answer it. The first
player to answer correctly receives a reward of quest points. All answers are
case-insensitive, and you only need to type enough of the answer to be unique.

Related Helps: Quest.
